comment:
* A NumberRangeFormatter that does not yet have a locale. In order to format, a locale must be specified.
 *
 * Instances of this class are immutable and thread-safe.
 *
 * @author sffc
 * @see NumberRangeFormatter

methods.name: public LocalizedNumberRangeFormatter locale(Locale locale)
methods.comment:
* Associate the given locale with the number range formatter. The locale is used for picking the * appropriate symbols, formats, and other data for number display. * *

* To use the Java default locale, call Locale.getDefault(): * * 

     * NumberFormatter.with(). ... .locale(Locale.getDefault())
     *
* * @param locale * The locale to use when loading data for number range formatting. * @return The fluent chain

methods.name: public LocalizedNumberRangeFormatter locale(ULocale locale)
methods.comment:
* ULocale version of the {@link #locale(Locale)} setter above.
     *
     * @param locale
     *            The locale to use when loading data for number range formatting.
     * @return The fluent chain
     * @see #locale(Locale)
